answers.answer: I'm 33w 2days and I'm the same way except I am getting contractions hit and miss.

33 weeks 1 day feeling the same and I have had a few comtractions here and there not to much to be worried but enough to think at my 36 week appt I'll likely be at least 1 cm dilated not that that means much but its a start with my 2 yr old went to the Dr at 36 weeks was 4 cm dilated had her at 37 weeks I've never went over 38 weeks with any of my children so hoping things will be working out in my favor in about 4-5 weeks Lol good luck ladies

I haven't been checked yet, but I have had some major pains and yesterday had contractions for a little over an hour. Hopefully we will all have safe and easy deliveries!!!
When Did your contractions start? And do you have them daily? I'm just scared cause I haven't been having any,at least that I know of..

Mine were in the evening. I have braxton hicks contractions about once a week. These were different bc I feel them lower and they were more like cramps. Nothing consistent. I didnt have contractions with my son. This pregnancy has been much different. My baby girl is very active. And I've had more medical issues. For instant I have gestational diabetes.  Due September 14th but I wonder some days if I will make it.
Ok I've woken up from sleep feeling crampy, but I didn't think of it as contractions because I thought contractions were tightening of the uterus...

question: I have had a great pregnancy so far, but starting to get a little worried because I'm not feeling any contractions yet. Right now I have rib pain, heart burn, and I get full so fast. The baby is moving like crazy and I have to pee all the time because baby keeps hitting my bladder.
